	<text>
		<body xml:lang="en">
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001261_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>4 Athol Place</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>Glasgow</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right"><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>28<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> Feby</p>
<lb/><p rend="right"><space extent="1" unit="words"/>1858</p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Dear <persName>Captain Washington</persName></p>
<lb/><p>The <term type="boat">Pearl</term> was 
<lb/>got of the slips 
<lb/>today and will 
<lb/>it is said proceed 
<lb/>to <placeName>Liverpool</placeName> on 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001261_0002"/><!--pb/@n='1v'--> 
<lb/><choice><reg>M</reg><orig>m</orig></choice>onday next. I have 
<lb/>therefore notified 
<lb/>the different members 
<lb/>to be at <placeName>Liverpool</placeName> 
<lb/>on Tuesday - I have 
<lb/>not written to 
<lb/><persName>Bedingfeld</persName> nor 
<lb/><persName>Baines</persName> as I suppose 
<lb/>they are there already<reg>.</reg> 
<lb/>We shall join 
<lb/>them on Wednesday 
<lb/>at noon - the 
<lb/>Captain who seems 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001261_0003"/><!--pb/@n='2r'--> 
<lb/>to be well qualified 
<lb/>for the work 
<lb/>thinks some stanchions 
<lb/>will be needed 
<lb/>to support the 
<lb/>weight of those 
<lb/>parts of the launch 
<lb/>which are placed 
<lb/>in the front part 
<lb/>of the steamer. She 
<lb/>looks well to a 
<lb/>landsman.</p>
<lb/><p>Please remember 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001261_0004"/><!--pb/@n='2v'--> 
<lb/>the order to <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi>
<lb/>Maclear</persName> for the 
<lb/>telescope and 
<lb/>oblige yours &amp;c<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>David Livingstone</p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">I enclose the last 
<lb/>account for presents 
<lb/>except one which 
<lb/>will be about 
<lb/>Â£10.</p>
			
